Roman.obverse_legend: IMP TRAIANO AVG GER DAC P M TR P
Roman.reverse_legend: COS V P P S P Q R OPTIMO PRINC PIET
Roman.obverse_desc: Bust of Trajan, laureate, draped on left shoulder, facing right
Roman.reverse_desc: Pietas, draped, veiled, standing left, with right hand dropping incense on lighted alter left, and holding sceptre in left hand

Roman.reverse_legend: P M TR P COS III SAL AVG
Roman.obverse_desc: Bust of Hadrian, laureate, draped, cuirassed, facing right
Roman.reverse_desc: Salus seated left, feeding serpent, who is wrapped around an altar, out of patera with right hand

Roman.obverse_legend: IMP CAES T AEL HADR ANTONINVS AVG PIVS P P
Roman.obverse_desc: Bust of Antoninus Pius, laureate, facing right
Roman.reverse_desc: Vesta, veiled, draped, standing left, holding simpulum in extended right hand and palladium at shoulder in left

Roman.obverse_desc: Bust of Septimius Severus, laureate, facing right
Roman.reverse_desc: Victory, winged, draped, advancing left, holding wreath in extended right hand and palm sloped over left shoulder in left hand

Roman.reverse_legend: PONTIF TR P VIII COS II
Roman.obverse_desc: Bust of Caracalla, laureate, draped, facing right
Roman.reverse_desc: Mars, helmeted, naked except for cloak on left shoulder, standing left, right foot set on helmet, holding branch in right hand and spear in left hand

Roman.obverse_desc: Bust of Severus Alexander, laureate, draped, facing right
Roman.reverse_desc: Mars, helmeted, walking right, carrying spear in right hand and shield in left hand

Roman.obverse_desc: Bust of Gordian III, radiate, draped, cuirassed, facing right
Roman.reverse_desc: Providentia, draped, standing left, holding wand in right hand over globe set on ground and sceptre in left hand

Roman.obverse_legend: IMP C P LIC VALERIANVS AVG
Roman.obverse_desc: Bust of Valerian, radiate, draped, facing right
Roman.reverse_desc: Fides, draped, standing left, holding two ensigns

Roman.obverse_desc: Radiate and cuirassed bust right, from the front
Roman.reverse_desc: Sol standing right, radiate, nude but for cloak over shoulders, raising branch in right, bow in left, left foot on captive

Roman.obverse_legend: D N VALENTINIANVS P F AVG
Roman.obverse_desc: Bust of Valentinian I, pearl-diademed, draped and cuirassed, facing right
Roman.reverse_desc: Victory advancing left, holding wreath and palm
